title: Tota Rani
text: Tota Rani is a small village near <a href="Dal%20Lake%20%28Himachal%20Pradesh%29">Dal Lake</a> in <a href="Kangra%20district">Kangra district</a>, <a href="Himachal%20Pradesh">Himachal Pradesh</a>, <a href="India">India</a>. It has a very long history of settlement by <a href="People%20of%20Nepal">Nepali people</a>. <a href="Thapa">Thapa</a> and <a href="Gurung">Gurung</a> culture are mixed here and now the Nepali culture almost vanished and people mingle with local <a href="Himachal%20Pradesh">Himachali</a> people, <a href="Gaddis">Gaddis</a>.
